trans-unit.source: "This version of Visual Studio works best with Internet Explorer 10 which is currently not installed on your computer."
trans-unit.target: "This version of Visual Studio works best with Internet Explorer 10 which is currently not installed on your computer."

trans-unit.source: Symptoms
trans-unit.target: Symptoms

trans-unit.source: You receive the error "This version of Visual Studio works best with Internet Explorer 10 which is currently not installed on your computer.
trans-unit.target: You receive the error "This version of Visual Studio works best with Internet Explorer 10 which is currently not installed on your computer.

trans-unit.source: If you choose to continue, some features might not work as expected.".
trans-unit.target: If you choose to continue, some features might not work as expected.".

trans-unit.source: Some Microsoft Visual Studio 2015 and Microsoft Visual Studio 2013 features do not work as expected when Internet Explorer 10 or a later version is not installed.
trans-unit.target: Some Microsoft Visual Studio 2015 and Microsoft Visual Studio 2013 features do not work as expected when Internet Explorer 10 or a later version is not installed.

trans-unit.source: This problem affects only Windows 7 users.
trans-unit.target: This problem affects only Windows 7 users.

trans-unit.source:
Users of Windows 8 and later versions are not affected because the required dependencies for the browser are built into those operating systems. The following features are known not to work as expected if Internet Explorer 10 or a later version is not installed:

Visual Studio 2013
trans-unit.target:
Users of Windows 8 and later versions are not affected because the required dependencies for the browser are built into those operating systems. The following features are known not to work as expected if Internet Explorer 10 or a later version is not installed:

Visual Studio 2013

trans-unit.source: • IntelliTrace: Performance Details page is not displayed as expected
trans-unit.target: • IntelliTrace: Performance Details page is not displayed as expected

trans-unit.source: • Debug Managed Memory displays a blank page and an error dialog box
trans-unit.target: • Debug Managed Memory displays a blank page and an error dialog box

trans-unit.source: • Load Testing by using Team Foundation Service: Load Test Runner results are not displayed as expected
trans-unit.target: • Load Testing by using Team Foundation Service: Load Test Runner results are not displayed as expected

trans-unit.source: • JavaScript Console and DOM Explorer windows are not displayed as expected
trans-unit.target: • JavaScript Console and DOM Explorer windows are not displayed as expected

trans-unit.source: Visual Studio 2015
trans-unit.target: Visual Studio 2015

trans-unit.source: • Debugger and diagnostics tools
trans-unit.target: • Debugger and diagnostics tools

trans-unit.source: • Cloud Explorer
trans-unit.target: • Cloud Explorer

trans-unit.source: Visual Studio 2013
trans-unit.target: Visual Studio 2013

trans-unit.source: IntelliTrace : Performance Details page is not displayed as expected
trans-unit.target: IntelliTrace : Performance Details page is not displayed as expected

trans-unit.source: When you use IntelliTrace to examine a log file that contains a performance violation event, you experience issues after you click to view more details about the violation.
trans-unit.target: When you use IntelliTrace to examine a log file that contains a performance violation event, you experience issues after you click to view more details about the violation.

trans-unit.source: The Performance Details page contains information about the execution tree of a performance violation event.
trans-unit.target: The Performance Details page contains information about the execution tree of a performance violation event.

trans-unit.source: However, if Internet Explorer 10 or a later version is not installed, the Execution Tree section is blank and you receive an error message.
trans-unit.target: However, if Internet Explorer 10 or a later version is not installed, the Execution Tree section is blank and you receive an error message.

trans-unit.source: Debug Managed Memory feature displays a blank page and an error message
trans-unit.target: Debug Managed Memory feature displays a blank page and an error message

trans-unit.source: When you open a managed dump file that contains heap information, the summary page includes a Debug Managed Memory option.
trans-unit.target: When you open a managed dump file that contains heap information, the summary page includes a Debug Managed Memory option.

trans-unit.source: If Internet Explorer 10 or a later version is not installed when you click this option, the document window that opens is blank and you receive an error message.
trans-unit.target: If Internet Explorer 10 or a later version is not installed when you click this option, the document window that opens is blank and you receive an error message.

trans-unit.source: If this occurs, you can safely ignore the error and close the document window.
trans-unit.target: If this occurs, you can safely ignore the error and close the document window.

trans-unit.source: Load Testing by using Team Foundation Service: Load Test Runner results are not displayed as expected
trans-unit.target: Load Testing by using Team Foundation Service: Load Test Runner results are not displayed as expected

trans-unit.source:
You do the following:
  • You run Load Testing by using Team Foundation Service.
trans-unit.target:
You do the following:
  • You run Load Testing by using Team Foundation Service.

trans-unit.source: • You select the Load Test Manager and Load Test Runner options.
trans-unit.target: • You select the Load Test Manager and Load Test Runner options.

trans-unit.source: If Internet Explorer 10 or a later version is not installed when you take these actions, the page that shows information about the test results is not displayed correctly.
trans-unit.target: If Internet Explorer 10 or a later version is not installed when you take these actions, the page that shows information about the test results is not displayed correctly.

trans-unit.source: JavaScript Console and DOM Explorer windows are not displayed as expected
trans-unit.target: JavaScript Console and DOM Explorer windows are not displayed as expected

trans-unit.source: When you use Visual Studio 2013 for Web development and you do not have Internet Explorer 11 installed, the JavaScript Console and DOM Explorer windows are not displayed as expected.
trans-unit.target: When you use Visual Studio 2013 for Web development and you do not have Internet Explorer 11 installed, the JavaScript Console and DOM Explorer windows are not displayed as expected.

trans-unit.source: These features require Internet Explorer 11.
trans-unit.target: These features require Internet Explorer 11.

trans-unit.source: If you are using Internet Explorer 10, you receive an error message that states that these features are unsupported by your current browser.
trans-unit.target: If you are using Internet Explorer 10, you receive an error message that states that these features are unsupported by your current browser.

trans-unit.source: If you are using Internet Explorer 9 or an earlier version, the browser window is blank but you do not receive the error message.
trans-unit.target: If you are using Internet Explorer 9 or an earlier version, the browser window is blank but you do not receive the error message.

trans-unit.source: Visual Studio 2015
trans-unit.target: Visual Studio 2015

trans-unit.source: Debugger and diagnostics tools
trans-unit.target: Debugger and diagnostics tools

trans-unit.source: When you debug an application in Visual Studio 2015, several new debugging tool windows are not displayed as expected and may also generate an error message.
trans-unit.target: When you debug an application in Visual Studio 2015, several new debugging tool windows are not displayed as expected and may also generate an error message.

trans-unit.source: These windows and tools include Diagnostics, CPU Usage, Memory Usage, and Application Timeline.
trans-unit.target: These windows and tools include Diagnostics, CPU Usage, Memory Usage, and Application Timeline.

trans-unit.source: Cloud Explorer
trans-unit.target: Cloud Explorer

trans-unit.source: If you install the Cloud Explorer for Visual Studio 2015, this new extension window to browse resources on Azure is not displayed correctly and may generate an error message.
trans-unit.target: If you install the Cloud Explorer for Visual Studio 2015, this new extension window to browse resources on Azure is not displayed correctly and may generate an error message.

trans-unit.source:
Cause
These problems occur because Visual Studio 2015 and Visual Studio 2013 have features that work best together with Internet Explorer 10 or later versions.
trans-unit.target:
Cause
These problems occur because Visual Studio 2015 and Visual Studio 2013 have features that work best together with Internet Explorer 10 or later versions.

trans-unit.source: If Internet Explorer 10 or a later version is not installed, these features do not work as expected.
trans-unit.target: If Internet Explorer 10 or a later version is not installed, these features do not work as expected.

trans-unit.source: Cause
trans-unit.target: Cause

trans-unit.source: These problems occur because Visual Studio 2015 and Visual Studio 2013 have features that work best together with Internet Explorer 10 or later versions.
trans-unit.target: These problems occur because Visual Studio 2015 and Visual Studio 2013 have features that work best together with Internet Explorer 10 or later versions.

trans-unit.source: If Internet Explorer 10 or a later version is not installed, these features do not work as expected.
trans-unit.target: If Internet Explorer 10 or a later version is not installed, these features do not work as expected.

trans-unit.source: Resolution
trans-unit.target: Resolution

trans-unit.source: To resolve these problems, install Internet Explorer 10.
trans-unit.target: To resolve these problems, install Internet Explorer 10.

trans-unit.source: For full support of JavaScript Console and DOM Explorer, install Internet Explorer 11.
trans-unit.target: For full support of JavaScript Console and DOM Explorer, install Internet Explorer 11.
